SIMPLE: sentient
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sentient
<hw>Sen"ti*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sentiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>sentire</ets> to
discern or perceive by the senses. See <er>Sense</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having a faculty, or faculties, of sensation and perception.</def>
<specif>Specif.</specif> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>, <def>especially
sensitive; <as>as, the <ex>sentient</ex> extremities of nerves, which
terminate in the various organs or tissues</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sentient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sentient
<hw>Sen"ti*ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who has the faculty of
perception; a sentient being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sentiently</ent>⟦br⟧
